{#
  Compliance heatmap: rows are the OWASP ASI top-10 categories, columns
  are the four cross-reference frameworks (NIST, EU AI Act, CSA AICM,
  ISO/IEC 42001). Each cell shows whether at least one finding in this
  run cites a control from that framework for the given ASI category
  (full hit = green), some related control (partial = pale green) or
  nothing (miss = blank gray).

  Context:
    frameworks   list[{ "key": "nist_ai_rmf", "label": "NIST AI RMF" }]
    matrix_rows  list[{ "asi": "ASI01",
                        "label": "Memory Poisoning",
                        "cells": [{"state": "hit"|"partial"|"miss",
                                   "controls": ["MS-2.6", ...]}, ...] }]
#}
<section class="section" id="compliance">
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="section-number">3.</span> Matriz de compliance cruzada</h2>

  <p style="font-size: 9.5pt; color: var(--argos-color-ink-700); margin-bottom: 4mm;">
    Cada celda indica la presencia en este run de un hallazgo cuya referencia
    de compliance invoca el control correspondiente. Verde solido es una
    cobertura directa; verde suave es una cobertura relacionada; celda vacia
    significa que ningun hallazgo cita ese marco para la categoria indicada.
  </p>

  <table class="compliance-matrix">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th style="text-align: left; padding-left: 3mm;">OWASP ASI</th>
        {% for fw in frameworks %}
        <th>{{ fw.label }}</th>
        {% endfor %}
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in matrix_rows %}
      <tr>
        <th>{{ row.asi }} &middot; {{ row.label }}</th>
        {% for cell in row.cells %}
        <td class="cov-{{ cell.state }}" title="{{ cell.controls | join(', ') }}">
          {% if cell.controls %}
            {{ cell.controls | join(', ') }}
          {% else %}
            &mdash;
          {% endif %}
        </td>
        {% endfor %}
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
